1. Guinea Pig

On the first three lines, you will recieve the quantity of food, hay and cover which you buy for a month(30 days).
On the fourth line, you will recieve the guinea pig weight.
Every day the pig eats 300gr of food. Every second day you first feeds the pet then gives it a certain amount of hay equal to 5% of the rest of the food.
On every third day, you put cover with a quantity 1/3 of it's weight.

Write a program to calculate whether the quantity of food, hay and cover will be enough for a month.
If you run out of food, hay or cover - end the program.


2. Shopping list

You will recieve an initial list with groceries separated by an exclamation mark.
After that you will be receiving 4 types of commands until you recieve "Go shopping!"
Commands:
1.Urgent *input* - add the item at the start of the list. If the item already exists, skip.
2.Unnecessary *input* - remove the item with the given name, only if it exists in the list.
3.Correct *input* *input* - if the item with the given old name exists, change it's name with the new one. Otherwise skip.
4.Rearrange *input* - if the grocery exists in the list, remove it from it's current position and add it at the end of the list. Otherwise skip.


3. Heart Delivery

You will recieve a string with even integers, separated by "@". - "@" is our neighborhood.
After that you will recieve a series of "Jump" commands until you recieve "Love!".
Every house in the neighborhood need a certain hearts delivered so they can celebrate. The integers in the neighborhood indicate those hearts.

We start from index 0 and we must jump by a given length. The commands will be formatted like this - Jump*length*
Everytime we jump from one to another index, the hearts will be decreased by 2
If the given length jump (index) is larger than the size given. We should start from index 0 again.
